author: CNN
description: Adam Carr, the former boyfriend of US Army Spc. Sarah Beckstrom — the National Guard member killed in an ambush-style attack in Washington, DC — spoke to CNN’s Gabe Cohen about her deployment to DC.
title: Slain National Guard member’s ex-boyfriend said she felt 'mixed' about DC deployment

author: CNN
description:
Activist groups including Indivisible, Until Freedom, and Black Voters Matter say that Target, Home Depot and Amazon have "caved to Donald Trump's. . .attacks on our communities and our values." They are calling for a pressure campaign and boycott dubbed "We Ain't Buying It."

CNN's Victor Blackwell speaks with LaTosha Brown, co-founder of Black Voters Matter and organizer of "We Ain't Buying It." #CNN #News
title: 'We Ain't Buying It': Boycotts take aim at businesses not opposing Trump

author: CNN
description:
Russia launched its largest barrage of drones and missiles in a month across Ukraine, killing at least three people, Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky said Saturday, as a Kyiv delegation heads to the United States for fresh peace talks. A flurry of diplomacy is taking place after a plan put forward by US President Donald Trump triggered alarm in Kyiv, as the original draft heavily favored Russia. The talks will be led from the Ukrainian side by Rustem Umerov, Secretary of the National Security and Defense Council of Ukraine, who Zelensky appointed following the resignation of his top aide on Friday. 

US Secretary of State Marco Rubio, special envoy Steve Witkoff, and Trump’s son-in-law Jared Kushner will meet the Ukrainian delegation in Miami, Florida this weekend, a White House official told CNN on Saturday.

CNN international correspondent Larry Madowo reports, Omar Jimenez speaks with former deputy assistant Secretary of State Joel Rubin and Isabel Rosales speaks with CNN glo
title: Russia launches largest drone assault on Ukraine in a month as Kyiv delegation heads to US for talks

description: As AI eliminates jobs at a historic pace, former 2020 presidential candidate Andrew Yang argues that universal basic income could help Americans adapt to the rapidly changing economy.                   #CNN #News
title: AI’s job shake-up is accelerating. Is it time for universal basic income?

description:
The Vancouver Police Department posted a video online that they say shows a rideshare driver helping a woman escape a "domestic-violence-related assault" in Washington state on November 15. Detectives are investigating the incident, police said.

#CNN #News #Vancouver #Washington
title: Rideshare driver helps woman escape from domestic violence

author: CNN
description:
Small businesses in Charlotte, North Carolina are hoping for a boost in sales on Small Business Saturday, especially after immigration raids in the Charlotte area which disrupted operations at some small immigrant-owned businesses.

CNN's Isabel Rosales speaks with Greg Asciutto, executive director of CharlotteEAST and CNN correspondent Ivan Rodriguez reports on the rising costs facing small business owners. Isabel Rosales also speaks with business writer Lisa Lacy about costs from tariffs and how businesses and consumers are using AI this holiday season.  #CNN #News
title: Charlotte's local shops hope for profits after ICE raids

author: CNN
description:
President Donald Trump is doubling down on the aggressive anti-immigration policies that helped deliver him a second term, launching an interagency federal investigation into the shooting of two National Guard members in Washington, DC, while also directing his administration to take steps to stem migration into the US.

CNN's Elex Michaelson speaks with Shawn VanDiver, founder and president of #AfghanEvac, on "The Story Is with Elex Michaelson." #CNN #News
title: US halts all asylum decisions after National Guard shooting

author: CNN
description:
As US President Donald Trump and Russian President Vladimir Putin both openly consider testing their countries’ nuclear weapons, a new Netflix movie explores how top US leaders might respond to a sudden foreign missile threat.

CNN’s Kaitlan Collins interviews "A House of Dynamite" director Kathryn Bigelow and screenwriter/producer Noah Oppenheim on "The Source."" #CNN #News
title: New movie depicts 18-minute countdown to nuclear impact

description:
